```
# Railway Deployment Checklist

## Pre-Deployment ✅

- [ ] GitHub account ready
- [ ] Repository created with Flask code
- [ ] All changes committed and pushed
- [ ] `.gitignore` includes `.env`
- [ ] No credentials in code

## Railway Setup ✅

- [ ] Railway account created
- [ ] New project created
- [ ] PostgreSQL service added
- [ ] Flask service added from GitHub
- [ ] Services connected

## Code Updates ✅

- [ ] `config.py` updated for Railway
- [ ] `run.py` updated for production
- [ ] `requirements.txt` includes gunicorn
- [ ] `Procfile` created
- [ ] `wsgi.py` created
- [ ] `.env.railway` template created
- [ ] `create_admin.py` created

## Environment Variables ✅

- [ ] DATABASE_URL set (from PostgreSQL service)
- [ ] FLASK_ENV set to "production"
- [ ] SECRET_KEY generated and set
- [ ] DEBUG set to False
- [ ] PORT set (Railway sets automatically)
- [ ] Other variables as needed

## Deployment ✅

- [ ] All files committed
- [ ] Push to main branch
- [ ] Railway auto-detects and builds
- [ ] Build completes successfully
- [ ] App shows as "Running" in dashboard
- [ ] URL accessible in browser

## Post-Deployment ✅

- [ ] Access application URL
- [ ] Check logs for errors
- [ ] Database migration completed
- [ ] Create admin user: `python create_admin.py`
- [ ] Test login functionality
- [ ] Test basic features

## Production Setup ✅

- [ ] Change admin password
- [ ] Set up monitoring
- [ ] Enable auto-deploy (if desired)
- [ ] Setup error notifications
- [ ] Document deployment URL

## Monitoring ✅

- [ ] Check Railway dashboard regularly
- [ ] Monitor application logs
- [ ] Monitor database usage
- [ ] Setup alerts if available
- [ ] Track performance metrics

---

## Quick Commands

### Deploy Update
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Update feature"
git push origin main
# Railway auto-deploys in 2-3 minutes
```

### Create Admin User
```bash
python create_admin.py
```

### Check Health
```bash
python health_check.py
```

### View Logs
Access Railway dashboard → Service → Logs tab

### Database Access
Access Railway dashboard → PostgreSQL service → Connect tab

---

## URLs

- **App URL:** `https://your-app-name.up.railway.app`
- **Railway Dashboard:** `https://railway.app`
- **GitHub Repo:** `https://github.com/your-username/app_lembaga`
- **PostgreSQL Service:** Available in Railway dashboard

---

## Support

- Railway Docs: https://docs.railway.app
- Flask Docs: https://flask.palletsprojects.com
- GitHub Help: https://docs.github.com

---

Status: Ready for deployment ✅
Last Updated: 2024
